Citations
Date: 31/12/1866
Source: Southland Times
Author:
Vol / Page: 2
Edition:
Quote: The land reformer who opposed the squatting system which gave the pastoral tenant a small principality at a nominal rent, argued with energy and ability, that by adopting a methodic system of cultivation [sic] English and other grasses on pastoral land, the productiveness of the land would be increased tenfold, and prove a preventative to scab, and the other diseases that afflict stock that are kept for a length of time on virgin pasture.
