Author:
Vol / Page: 5
Edition:
Quote: I am as warmly a land reformer as ever I was, but I am less hopeful of seeing an end to the squatting system than formerly.
Notes:

Date: 21/5/1885
Source: Hawke's Bay Herald
Author:
Vol / Page: 4
Edition:
Quote: He quoted from published lectures of the late Lord Lyttelton, certain experiences of his Lordship during a visit to Canterbury in 1868, when he visited a run of Mr Charles Harper, which run contained about 50,000 acres, and explains the old squatting system, with pre-emptive rights, spotting sections, &c., all of which will be familiar to Hawke's Bay readers.
